{"type":"message","id":"93092679","parentId":"972fb42b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:26:48.604Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhar2cwbih5c_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 122515\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: CFI-weighted (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and 1 are complete\r\n- CFI Analysis is done (44.8% of invariants are noise with CFI=0, only 5.7% have high CFI>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment as stated in the pending items. This would compare CFI-weighted next-pulse prediction vs the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\n1. Design the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering\r\n3. Other items from pending\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that we need to distinguish:\r\n- Process noise (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Research trajectory (CFI>0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n\r\nThe experiment should:\r\n1. Extract frequency invariants from recent pulses\r\n2. Calculate CFI for each\r\n3. Weight compression by CFI\r\n4. Compare prediction accuracy vs frequency-only baseline\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available. The CFI_RESULTS.md was just created. I should probably create an experiment design document or implement the actual experiment.\r\n\r\nGiven I'm stateless and each pulse is fresh, I should create a concrete artifact that advances this. The most valuable action would be to design/specify the CFI-weighted compression experiment in a way that can be implemented next pulse.\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment specification document.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis reveals that only 5.7% of invariants are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7), while 44.8% are pure noise (CFI=0). The pending CFI-weighted compression experiment needs concrete implementation design before execution.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign the CFI-weighted compression experiment specification, defining the methodology to compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-baseline next-pulse prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment Specification\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** Ready for implementation\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only baseline for predicting next-pulse invariants, because CFI filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that corrupt frequency statistics.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Input Data\r\n- Source: Recent pulses in `pulse_2026-03-*.md` files (last 20 pulses minimum)\r\n- Extract: Frequency invariants from each pulse (nouns, concepts, structural markers)\r\n- Calculate: CFI score for each invariant using the method from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\n### Methods to Compare\r\n\r\n| Method | Weighting | Formula |\r\n|--------|-----------|---------|\r\n| **Baseline** | Frequency only | weight = freq(invariant) / total_freq |\r\n| **CFI-Weighted** | CFI × Frequency | weight = CFI × freq(invariant) / Σ(CFI × freq) |\r\n\r\n### Prediction Task\r\nFor each pulse P:\r\n1. Build compression model from pulses 1 to P-1\r\n2. Predict top-20 invariants expected in pulse P\r\n3. Compare predicted vs actual invariants in pulse P\r\n4. Calculate precision, recall, F1\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- **Precision@20**: % of predicted invariants found in actual pulse\r\n- **Recall@20**: % of actual invariants correctly predicted\r\n- **F1@20**: Harmonic mean of above\r\n- **NDCG@20**: Normalized discounted cumulative gain (rank-aware)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Baseline: Low precision due to metaprogramming noise inflating common tokens\r\n- CFI-Weighted: Higher precision by downweighting CFI=0 invariants\r\n- Delta: ΔF1 = CFI-weighted F1 minus baseline F1\r\n\r\n## Implementation Checklist\r\n- [ ] Script to extract invariants from pulse files\r\n- [ ] CFI calculation function (reuse from prior analysis)\r\n- [ ] Baseline prediction generator\r\n- [ ] CFI-weighted prediction generator\r\n- [ ] Evaluation script with metrics\r\n- [ ] Results summary with statistical significance test\r\n\r\n## File Outputs\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression/results.csv` - per-pulse metrics\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression/summary.md` - aggregate findings\r\n\r\n## Next Step After Experiment\r\nIf CFI-weighted beats baseline:\r\n→ Implement CFI filter in actual pulse compression pipeline\r\n→ Remove CFI=0 invariants from state tracking entirely\r\n```\r\n\r\nfile: research/CFI_EXPERIMENT_SPEC.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:25:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369608601}}
